* Shift from {{m|ja|大|tr=ō-||[[big]], [[great]]}} + {{m|ja|水|tr=mi||[[water]]|pos=combining form}}.<ref>{{R:Nipponica}}</ref>
: This is problematic phonetically because there is no known term having a related shift from {{IPAchar|/opo/}} → {{IPAchar|/oː/}} → {{IPAchar|/o/}} → {{IPAchar|/u/}}, and semantically as there already exists a compound {{m|ja|大水|tr=ōmizu||[[flood]]}}.
* From {{m|ja|う|tr=u-|pos=stem indicating “[[ocean]]”}} + {{m|ja|水|tr=mi||water|pos=combining form}}. The ''u-'' stem is evident in {{m|ja|魚|tr=uo||[[fish]]}} and {{m|ja|潮|tr=ushio||[[salt water]]; [[tide]]}}, and in the {{m|ja|海|tr=una}} element in various ancient terms (see below).

